This video made my heart happy. I'm Maltese and this just made me happy. I just wanted to mention a few things that you guys could have enjoyed more. The Pastizzi that you ate arent the original. Great video sort of... But! You ate the wrong Pastizz (Pastizzi is plural). The pastry is not the proper one as is the shape, although the Cordina Pastizzi are delicious (but very expensive). Also the hot thick chocolate is totally Italian, nothing Maltese in it. The rabbit (as a local) looked disgusting and we never get a gravy bowl to pour on it. The widow soup looked totally wrong (but then again you ate at a tourist restaurant. And you never went out of Valletta to eat. You needed to go to the villages, the band clubs, restaurants that locals go to and to Gozo. And for Rabbit, the closest to home made would be the village of Mgarr where a few restaurants get it right and are frequented by the locals. You never tried our other national dish Octopus Stew. Oh and the sausage dish is not something we eat much at all. And it's Cisk (pronounced CHisk). And that's absolutely NOT how we eat Ftira. That's italian pizza toppings on Ftira bread. And not one plate of fresh Mediterranean fish or our most popular Pasta dishes,  'Ravjul' , Timpana, etc.... Sacrilege....
